    "num": "03",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">03</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Source Reliability</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Evaluating the Trustworthiness of Texican Historical Sources</h2><ul><li>Biases in contemporary accounts and official records</li><li>Inconsistencies between primary and secondary sources</li><li>Challenges in verifying authenticity and authorship</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Many sources about Texicans were created by outsiders or political actors with agendas, requiring careful scrutiny to assess reliability and bias. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s6\">[6]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A military report from the Texas Revolution may depict Texicans differently than a personal letter from a Texican participant.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Compare two contrasting accounts of a Texican event and identify potential biases.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Accepting all historical sources at face value without considering context or perspective.</p></div></div>",
