    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">09</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Application</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Applying Critical Evaluation to a Texican Source</h2><ul><li>Analyze a provided primary source excerpt on Texican life</li><li>Identify potential biases and gaps</li><li>Suggest complementary sources to verify information</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Hands-on source analysis reinforces critical evaluation skills and deepens understanding of Texican history. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s10\">[10]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s11\">[11]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Examine a Texican land deed for language reflecting political or cultural bias.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Write a brief critique of the source’s reliability and completeness.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Failing to consider the source’s historical context and creator’s perspective.</p></div><div id=\"quiz-slide57\" class=\"quizbox popquiz anim\" data-quiz=\"[{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;mc&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:2,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Which statement correctly distinguishes &#39;Texican&#39; from &#39;Texian&#39; and &#39;Texan&#39;?&quot;,&quot;options&quot;:[&quot;&#39;Texican&#39; refers to early Spanish-speaking settlers; &#39;Texian&#39; was used for Anglo settlers during the Texas Revolution; &#39;Texan&#39; is the modern term for all residents of Texas.&quot;,&quot;&#39;Texican&#39; and &#39;Texian&#39; are interchangeable terms for all Texas settlers; &#39;Texan&#39; refers only to native-born Texans.&quot;,&quot;&#39;Texan&#39; was the original term for settlers; &#39;Texican&#39; and &#39;Texian&#39; are modern terms.&quot;,&quot;&#39;Texian&#39; refers to Mexican settlers; &#39;Texican&#39; refers to Anglo settlers; &#39;Texan&#39; is unrelated.&quot;],&quot;answer&quot;:0,&quot;why&quot;:&quot;This option accurately reflects historical usage and distinctions among the terms as taught.&quot;},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;sa&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:3,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Explain the role of Texicans in the Texas Revolution and how their political allegiances were complex.&quot;,&quot;rubric&quot;:&quot;A complete answer should describe Texican participation in military and political events, mention their cultural background, and discuss their divided loyalties between Mexico and Texas independence.&quot;,&quot;sample&quot;:&quot;Texicans, as Spanish-speaking settlers, played key roles in battles and political movements during the Texas Revolution. Their allegiances were complex because many identified culturally with Mexico but also supported Texas independence due to local interests.&quot;,&quot;accept&quot;:[&quot;Texicans fought in the revolution with mixed loyalties to Mexico and Texas&quot;,&quot;They were culturally Mexican but politically divided during the revolution&quot;,&quot;Texicans participated in key battles and had complex political positions&quot;]}]\" data-pop=\"1\"></div></div>",
